content:
TITLE: Basic Twig Usage with ArrayLoader
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic Twig API usage with ArrayLoader to render a simple template. Shows template creation, variable passing, and rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/intro.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
require_once '/path/to/vendor/autoload.php';

$loader = new \Twig\Loader\ArrayLoader([
    'index' => 'Hello {{ name }}!',
]);
$twig = new \Twig\Environment($loader);

echo $twig->render('index', ['name' => 'Fabien']);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Defining a Base Template with Blocks in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a base 'skeleton' template with blocks that can be overridden by child templates. This example defines an HTML structure with blocks for head, title, content, and footer.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        {% block head %}
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"/>
            <title>{% block title %}{% endblock %} - My Webpage</title>
        {% endblock %}
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="content">{% block content %}{% endblock %}</div>
        <div id="footer">
            {% block footer %}
                &copy; Copyright 2011 by <a href="https://example.com/">you</a>.
            {% endblock %}
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Setting Variables in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to set variables in Twig using the set tag. Shows examples of setting string, array, and map variables.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% set name = 'Fabien' %}
{% set numbers = [1, 2] %}
{% set map = {'city': 'Paris'} %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Initializing Twig Environment with Filesystem Loader in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Creates a Twig environment with a filesystem loader, specifying the template directory and cache location. This is the typical setup for configuring Twig in an application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/api.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
require_once '/path/to/vendor/autoload.php';

$loader = new \Twig\Loader\FilesystemLoader('/path/to/templates');
$twig = new \Twig\Environment($loader, [
    'cache' => '/path/to/compilation_cache',
]);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic Twig Template Structure in HTML
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic structure of a Twig template, including variable output, loops, and HTML markup. Shows the usage of Twig delimiters {% %} for logic and {{ }} for output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>My Webpage</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <ul id="navigation">
        {% for item in navigation %}
            <li><a href="{{ item.href }}">{{ item.caption }}</a></li>
        {% endfor %}
        </ul>

        <h1>My Webpage</h1>
        {{ a_variable }}
    </body>
</html>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding Global Variables to Twig Environment
DESCRIPTION: PHP code example showing how to add a global variable to a Twig environment that can be accessed in all templates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/advanced.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$twig = new \Twig\Environment($loader);
$twig->addGlobal('text', new Text());
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using the parent() Function in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the parent() function to render the contents of the parent block within a child template's block.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% block sidebar %}
    <h3>Table Of Contents</h3>
    ...
    {{ parent() }}
{% endblock %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using HTML Escaping in Twig Templates
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of the escape filter to escape HTML content. This is the default escaping strategy used to prevent XSS attacks when outputting user data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/filters/escape.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<p>
    {{ user.username|escape }}
</p>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Extending a Base Template in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend a base template and override specific blocks. This child template extends 'base.html.twig' and provides content for the title, head, and content blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Index{% endblock %}
{% block head %}
    {{ parent() }}
    <style type="text/css">
        .important { color: #336699; }
    </style>
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h1>Index</h1>
    <p class="important">
        Welcome to my awesome homepage.
    </p>
{% endblock %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Twig Usage with FilesystemLoader
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use Twig with FilesystemLoader to load templates from filesystem, including cache configuration and template rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/intro.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$loader = new \Twig\Loader\FilesystemLoader('/path/to/templates');
$twig = new \Twig\Environment($loader, [
    'cache' => '/path/to/compilation_cache',
]);

echo $twig->render('index.html.twig', ['name' => 'Fabien']);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using PHP Attributes to Define Twig Extensions
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use PHP attributes to define filters, functions, and tests in a Twig extension. This approach simplifies the extension definition process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/advanced.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_31

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
use Twig\Attribute\AsTwigFilter;
use Twig\Attribute\AsTwigFunction;
use Twig\Attribute\AsTwigTest;

class ProjectExtension
{
    #[AsTwigFilter('rot13')]
    public static function rot13(string $string): string
    {
        // ...
    }

    #[AsTwigFunction('lipsum')]
    public static function lipsum(int $count): string
    {
        // ...
    }

    #[AsTwigTest('even')]
    public static function isEven(int $number): bool
    {
        // ...
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Control Structures in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows examples of control structures in Twig, including for loops and if statements. Demonstrates how to iterate over arrays and check conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<h1>Members</h1>
<ul>
    {% for user in users %}
        <li>{{ user.username|e }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
</ul>
```

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% if users|length > 0 %}
    <ul>
        {% for user in users %}
            <li>{{ user.username|e }}</li>
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
{% endif %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Base Template Structure in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Defines a basic HTML skeleton document with blocks that can be overridden by child templates. Includes blocks for head, title, content and footer sections.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/extends.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        {% block head %}
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"/>
            <title>{% block title %}{% endblock %} - My Webpage</title>
        {% endblock %}
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="content">{% block content %}{% endblock %}</div>
        <div id="footer">
            {% block footer %}
                &copy; Copyright 2011 by <a href="https://example.com/">you</a>.
            {% endblock %}
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Loading and Rendering Twig Templates in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to load a template from the Twig environment and render it with variables. Also shows direct rendering through the environment and rendering individual blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/api.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
$template = $twig->load('index.html.twig');

echo $template->render(['the' => 'variables', 'go' => 'here']);

echo $twig->render('index.html.twig', ['the' => 'variables', 'go' => 'here']);

echo $template->renderBlock('block_name', ['the' => 'variables', 'go' => 'here']);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Conditional Template Inheritance
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates conditional inheritance based on variable evaluation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/extends.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% extends standalone ? "minimum.html.twig" : "base.html.twig" %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic If Statement in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a simple if statement in Twig to check if a boolean expression is false. This example shows how to display a maintenance message when the 'online' variable is false.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/if.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% if online == false %}
    <p>Our website is in maintenance mode. Please, come back later.</p>
{% endif %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Naming Conventions in Twig Templates
DESCRIPTION: Shows proper naming conventions for variables, functions, filters, and arguments in Twig. Use snake case for all variable names, function/filter/test names, and argument names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/coding_standards.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% set name = 'Fabien' %}
{% set first_name = 'Fabien' %}

{{ 'Fabien Potencier'|to_lower_case }}
{{ generate_random_number() }}

{% macro html_input(class_name) %}

{{ html_input(class_name: 'pwd') }}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Twig Arrow Functions
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of arrow functions for mapping and filtering operations
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ people|map(p => p.first_name)|join(', ') }}

{% set first_name_fn = (p) => p.first_name %}

{{ people|map(first_name_fn)|join(', ') }}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing Filesystem Loader with Multiple Paths in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a filesystem loader with multiple template directories, and how to add or prepend paths. Also demonstrates using namespaced templates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/api.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
$loader = new \Twig\Loader\FilesystemLoader([$templateDir1, $templateDir2]);

$loader->addPath($templateDir3);
$loader->prependPath($templateDir4);

$loader->addPath($templateDir, 'admin');

$twig->render('@admin/index.html.twig', []);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Registering a Twig Extension in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to register a custom Twig extension with the Twig Environment using the addExtension() method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/advanced.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_25

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
$twig = new \Twig\Environment($loader);
$twig->addExtension(new CustomTwigExtension());
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using trim Filter in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates various ways to use the trim filter in Twig templates. It shows how to trim whitespace from both ends, trim specific characters, and trim from left or right side only.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/filters/trim.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ '  I like Twig.  '|trim }}

{# outputs 'I like Twig.' #}

{{ '  I like Twig.'|trim('.') }}

{# outputs '  I like Twig' #}

{{ '  I like Twig.  '|trim(side: 'left') }}

{# outputs 'I like Twig.  ' #}

{{ '  I like Twig.  '|trim(' ', 'right') }}

{# outputs '  I like Twig.' #}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Using parent() Function in Twig Block Override
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to extend a base template and override a block while preserving the parent block's content using the parent() function. The example shows a sidebar block that adds a heading while maintaining the original sidebar content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/functions/parent.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block sidebar %}
    <h3>Table Of Contents</h3>
    ...
    {{ parent() }}
{% endblock %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Accessing Loop Variables in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to access special loop variables inside a Twig for loop, such as index and first/last iteration flags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/for.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% for user in users %}
    {{ loop.index }} - {{ user.username }}
{% endfor %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying Filters in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to apply filters to variables and expressions in Twig. Demonstrates chaining filters and using filters with arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ name|striptags|title }}
```

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ list|join(', ') }}
```

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% apply upper %}
    This text becomes uppercase
{% endapply %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Demonstrating Twig Operator Usage
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases the usage of various Twig operators mentioned in the table. It includes examples of the spread operator, filter calls, function calls, attribute access, array access, and other arithmetic and logical operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/operators_precedence.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ ...array }}
{{ variable | filter }}
{{ function() }}
{{ object.attribute }}
{{ array[index] }}
{{ -number }}
{{ +number }}
{{ a ?? b }}
{{ x => x * 2 }}
{{ 2 ** 3 }}
{{ value is defined }}
{{ value is not null }}
{{ 10 * 5 }}
{{ 20 / 4 }}
{{ 7 // 2 }}
{{ 10 % 3 }}
{{ not condition }}
{{ 'Hello ' ~ 'World' }}
{{ 5 + 3 }}
{{ 10 - 4 }}
{{ 1..5 }}
{{ a == b }}
{{ a != b }}
{{ a <=> b }}
{{ a < b }}
{{ a > b }}
{{ a >= b }}
{{ a <= b }}
{{ a not in array }}
{{ a in array }}
{{ string matches '/pattern/' }}
{{ string starts with 'prefix' }}
{{ string ends with 'suffix' }}
{{ array has some element }}
{{ array has every required_element }}
{{ a b-and b }}
{{ a b-xor b }}
{{ a b-or b }}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Validating Twig Template Syntax
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to validate Twig template syntax before saving or processing. Includes error handling for syntax validation of single templates and multiple files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/recipes.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
try {
    $twig->parse($twig->tokenize(new \Twig\Source($template)));
    // the $template is valid
} catch (\Twig\Error\SyntaxError $e) {
    // $template contains one or more syntax errors
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Twig String Pattern Matching
DESCRIPTION: Examples of string pattern matching using 'starts with', 'ends with', and regular expressions
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% if 'Fabien' starts with 'F' %}
{% endif %}

{% if 'Fabien' ends with 'n' %}
{% endif %}

{% if phone matches '/^[\\d\\.]+$/' %}
{% endif %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Demonstrating Verbatim Tag Usage in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to wrap Twig syntax in verbatim tags to display it as raw text without parsing. The example demonstrates a common loop pattern that would normally be processed by Twig, but is instead displayed literally.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/verbatim.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% verbatim %}
    <ul>
    {% for item in seq %}
        <li>{{ item }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
    </ul>
{% endverbatim %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Defining Form Input Macros in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Defines reusable macros for rendering HTML form inputs and textareas with configurable parameters. Shows how to create macros with default parameter values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/macro.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% macro input(name, value, type = "text", size = 20) %}
    <input type="{{ type }}" name="{{ name }}" value="{{ value|e }}" size="{{ size }}"/>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro textarea(name, value, rows = 10, cols = 40) %}
    <textarea name="{{ name }}" rows="{{ rows }}" cols="{{ cols }}">{{ value|e }}</textarea>
{% endmacro %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Installing Twig via Composer
DESCRIPTION: Command to install Twig version 3.x using Composer package manager.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/intro.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
composer require "twig/twig:^3.0"
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Checking Variable Iterability in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the 'is iterable' test to conditionally handle both iterable and non-iterable variables. The code includes a loop for iterable variables and fallback behavior for non-iterable values like strings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tests/iterable.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{# evaluates to true if the users variable is iterable #}
{% if users is iterable %}
    {% for user in users %}
        Hello {{ user }}!
    {% endfor %}
{% else %}
    {# users is probably a string #}
    Hello {{ users }}!
{% endif %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Setting Up Functional Tests for Twig Extensions
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create functional tests for Twig extensions by implementing an IntegrationTestCase class. The example shows the test structure and file organization required for comprehensive testing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/advanced.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
namespace Project\Tests;

use Twig\Test\IntegrationTestCase;

class IntegrationTest extends IntegrationTestCase
{
    public function getExtensions()
    {
        return [
            new CustomTwigExtension1(),
            new CustomTwigExtension2(),
        ];
    }

    public function getFixturesDir()
    {
        return __DIR__.'/Fixtures/';
    }
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Multiple Variable Assignment in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to assign values to multiple variables in a single set statement.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/set.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% set first, last = 'Fabien', 'Potencier' %}

{# is equivalent to #}

{% set first = 'Fabien' %}
{% set last = 'Potencier' %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Specifying Escaping Strategy in Twig Templates
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the escape filter with an explicit HTML strategy parameter. This example shows both the shorthand and full syntax for HTML escaping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/filters/escape.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ user.username|e }}
{# is equivalent to #}
{{ user.username|e('html') }}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Iterating Over Keys and Values in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to access both keys and values while iterating over a sequence in Twig.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/for.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<h1>Members</h1>
<ul>
    {% for key, user in users %}
        <li>{{ key }}: {{ user.username|e }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
</ul>
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Child Template Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to extend a base template and override specific blocks. Demonstrates usage of parent() function to inherit base content while adding new content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/extends.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Index{% endblock %}
{% block head %}
    {{ parent() }}
    <style type="text/css">
        .important { color: #336699; }
    </style>
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h1>Index</h1>
    <p class="important">
        Welcome on my awesome homepage.
    </p>
{% endblock %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Twig Test Operator Usage
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of 'is' operator for testing variables against expressions
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{# find out if a variable is odd #}

{{ name is odd }}

{% if post.status is constant('Post::PUBLISHED') %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring Twig Safe Classes
DESCRIPTION: Example of marking classes and interfaces as safe for specific escaping strategies
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/api.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
$escaper->addSafeClass('HtmlGenerator', ['html']);
$escaper->addSafeClass('HtmlGeneratorInterface', ['html']);
$escaper->addSafeClass('HtmlGenerator', ['html', 'js']);
$escaper->addSafeClass('HtmlGenerator', ['all']);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Applying url_encode Filter to Strings and Mappings in Twig
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the usage of the url_encode filter in Twig for encoding URL segments and query strings. It shows examples of encoding a path segment with special characters, a string with spaces, and a mapping as a query string.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/filters/url_encode.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{{ "path-seg*ment"|url_encode }}
{# outputs "path-seg%2Ament" #}

{{ "string with spaces"|url_encode }}
{# outputs "string%20with%20spaces" #}

{{ {'name': 'Fabien', 'city': 'Paris'}|url_encode }}
{# outputs "name=Fabien&city=Paris" #}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Rendering Blocks Multiple Times in Twig Templates
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define a block and then render it multiple times within a template using the 'block' function. This is useful when working with template inheritance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/functions/block.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<title>{% block title %}{% endblock %}</title>

<h1>{{ block('title') }}</h1>

{% block body %}{% endblock %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Literal Expressions in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Shows examples of various literal expressions in Twig, including strings, numbers, sequences, and mappings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/templates.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{# keys as string #}
{'name': 'Fabien', 'city': 'Paris'}

{# keys as names (equivalent to the previous mapping) #}
{name: 'Fabien', city: 'Paris'}

{# keys as integer #}
{2: 'Twig', 4: 'Symfony'}

{# keys can be omitted if it is the same as the variable name #}
{Paris}
{# is equivalent to the following #}
{'Paris': Paris}

{# keys as expressions (the expression must be enclosed into parentheses) #}
{% set key = 'name' %}
{(key): 'Fabien', (1 + 1): 2, ('ci' ~ 'ty'): 'city'}
```

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% set complex = [1, {"name": "Fabien"}] %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Basic Template Include in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Simple example of including header and footer templates in a Twig file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/include.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: twig
CODE:
```
{% include 'header.html.twig' %}
    Body
{% include 'footer.html.twig' %}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Iterating Over Keys in Twig
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to iterate over the keys of a sequence using the 'keys' filter in Twig.
SOURCE: https://github.com/twigphp/Twig/blob/3.x/doc/tags/for.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
<h1>Members</h1>
<ul>
    {% for key in users|keys %}
